00:54.184 --> 00:55.524
Hi.

00:55.700 --> 00:57.458
I'm Damon.

00:57.856 --> 00:59.880
And I have anger issues.

00:59.973 --> 01:01.161
All: Hi, Damon.

01:01.203 --> 01:03.184
Man: Why don't you tell us
about what brought you

01:03.209 --> 01:04.254
to the meeting today?

01:04.280 --> 01:06.286
Well, I got my brother
this job...

01:06.356 --> 01:07.895
Actually, I asked for the job.

01:07.959 --> 01:10.529
Yeah. Through my connections.

01:10.895 --> 01:13.801
Anyway, our boss
gave Stefan new orders.

01:13.864 --> 01:15.731
And now, we're supposed
to push people

01:15.794 --> 01:18.489
to make evil choices,
and only then do we

01:18.559 --> 01:21.114
kill them and send
their souls to the devil.

01:21.231 --> 01:22.895
(Taps Damon) I thought
we were going for like, a...

01:22.919 --> 01:25.981
- A veiled analogy.
- Oh, they're all compelled.

01:26.059 --> 01:28.426
Clarity over cleverness.
That's what I always say.

01:28.481 --> 01:31.528
You've literally
never said that before.

01:31.637 --> 01:33.801
Anyway, since he got
this new job,

01:33.887 --> 01:36.567
- he's been difficult. Full of himself.
- Okay.

01:36.700 --> 01:39.468
He's just jealous because I'm
better at finding new clients.

01:39.501 --> 01:41.832
For instance. Who would you say
is the worst person in this room?

01:41.856 --> 01:43.841
Huh? Meg or Elizabeth?

01:43.887 --> 01:46.450
You both have said some pretty
awful things. I'm sure that,

01:46.512 --> 01:48.177
given the right opportunity,

01:48.210 --> 01:49.953
one of them would make
an evil choice.

01:50.031 --> 01:52.294
Small potatoes. I don't
even think they make the cut.

01:52.333 --> 01:54.183
Uh...
Uh! Elizabeth. Quiet.

01:54.216 --> 01:56.351
- You too, Meg.
- What about you? What if

01:56.398 --> 01:58.093
you had to pick
one person to die?

01:58.179 --> 01:59.804
Who would it be?
Meg or Elizabeth?

01:59.867 --> 02:02.453
- Wait, stop right there.
- What if it was between you

02:02.507 --> 02:03.648
and Meg?

02:03.695 --> 02:05.227
Would you want Meg to die?

02:05.260 --> 02:07.701
♪♪

02:07.854 --> 02:10.723
Answer the question honestly.

02:12.140 --> 02:13.763
Yes.

02:14.591 --> 02:16.105
I would want her to die

02:16.138 --> 02:17.506
instead of me.

02:18.469 --> 02:19.770
Whoa.

02:20.701 --> 02:21.945
What if both

02:22.025 --> 02:24.388
Meg and Elizabeth
had to die, in order

02:24.460 --> 02:26.162
for you to live?

02:28.044 --> 02:30.385
Then I'd want them both to die.

02:30.410 --> 02:32.974
Whoa. What if
we threw in everybody?

02:33.028 --> 02:35.864
Choose between yourself
and these people.

02:35.936 --> 02:37.938
I want to live.

02:39.591 --> 02:41.863
I don't care about any of them.

02:44.273 --> 02:45.909
Mm.

02:46.896 --> 02:48.146
- (Exhales)
- Stefan: Wow.

02:48.255 --> 02:50.973
Yeah. I think I've heard enough.

02:51.013 --> 02:52.977
Yeah. Me, too.

02:53.235 --> 02:54.242
(Screaming)

02:54.316 --> 02:56.085
(Crunching)

03:06.196 --> 03:07.664
Damon: Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

03:07.860 --> 03:09.524
I thought we were
only giving Cade

03:09.558 --> 03:11.711
the worst of the
worst, like this guy.

03:11.828 --> 03:13.295
Cade can have him.

03:13.390 --> 03:14.625
These are mine.

03:15.664 --> 03:17.030
What are you doing?

03:17.103 --> 03:18.103
Meditating?

03:18.142 --> 03:19.978
It's called self-control, Damon.

03:20.203 --> 03:22.399
No dripping blood
equals no temptation.

03:22.539 --> 03:24.438
I'm doing it right this time.

03:24.594 --> 03:26.735
Heads will remain intact.

03:26.844 --> 03:28.547
That's a very fine line.

03:28.617 --> 03:31.013
- Or a very fine neck membrane.
- You know,

03:31.045 --> 03:32.720
your lack of faith in me
is really starting

03:32.744 --> 03:33.719
to get on my nerves.

03:33.745 --> 03:35.766
I'm just saying, you
have a ripper history.

03:35.958 --> 03:39.195
Are you sure you want to keep
testing the blood-soaked waters?

03:39.291 --> 03:40.626
That's why it's called history.

03:40.722 --> 03:42.656
It won't repeat.

03:42.867 --> 03:44.960
I'm all good.

03:47.171 --> 03:49.173
(Exhaling)

03:49.735 --> 03:51.661
(Crunches)

03:53.602 --> 03:56.205
Yeah. I can see that.

